<h3 class=3D"wp-block-heading" id=3D"h-beer-bitterness-wars">Beer Bitternes=
s Wars?</h3>



<p>The pursuit of hoppiness has created a literally bitter rivalry between =
breweries.</p>



<p>Flying Monkeys Brewery of Ontario currently leads the pack with =E2=80=
=9CAlpha Fornication,=E2=80=9D which clocks in at 2500 IBUs, blowing runner=
-up Mikkeller=E2=80=99s =E2=80=9CHop Juice X 2007 IBU=E2=80=9D out of the w=
ater.</p>



<p>What none of these breweries explicitly state is that the human palate c=
an only distinguish up to around 110 IBUs when perceiving the bitterness le=
vel of a beer before it tucks into its shell and retreats down the esophagu=
s. While finding cheap beer might be hard, <a href=3D"https://www.everypayj=
oy.com/">this website</a> makes it easy with their coupons.</p>



<p>It could be argued that IBUs have become as much a marketing ploy as a t=
ool to better help beer drinkers understanding the beverage they are consum=
ing. So if IBUs aren=E2=80=99t entirely useful to the common drinker, is th=
ere a better scale?</p>



<p>=E2=80=9CI do think IBUs can be overstated, and therefore can be mislead=
ing to the consumer=E2=80=9D said Kevin McNerney, co-founder of SweetWater =
Brewing Co. and brewmaster at <a href=3D"https://www.gloverparkbrewery.com/=
">Glover Park Brewery</a>.</p>



<p>McNerney suggests an accompanying scale to define hop aroma, but in the =
end, =E2=80=9CWhat=E2=80=99s in the bottle is most important.=E2=80=9D</p>



<p>John Isenhour, Associate Professor of <a href=3D"https://bioinnovation.k=
ennesaw.edu/research/brewing-science.php">Brewing Science at Kennesaw State=
 University</a>, agrees that the best way to measure a beer=E2=80=99s quali=
ties are with the five senses.</p>



<p>=E2=80=9CWith taste preferences and abilities all over the map, I=E2=80=
=99m not sure that IBUs in the current state of craft brewing tells the con=
sumer an awful lot. My advice: just try a sample at the right temperature.=
=E2=80=9D</p>



<p>To the brewer, beer is art, and art cannot be quantified. Treat IBUs lik=
e an art critique: a resource for insight and appreciation. But take them w=
ith a grain of salt. After all, beauty is in the eye of the beer-holder.</p=
>



<hr class=3D"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity is-style-wide">



<h3 class=3D"wp-block-heading" id=3D"h-beer-styles-and-their-ibu-ranges">Be=
er Styles and Their IBU Ranges</h3>



<p>Different styles of beer all have different IBU levels and perceived bit=
terness levels to drinkers. Check out this list of popular beer styles and =
their respective IBU ranges.</p>



<p><a href=3D"https://beerconnoisseur.com/beer-styles/american-light-lager"=
><strong>Light Lager</strong></a>: IBUs =E2=80=93 10-20</p>



<p><a href=3D"https://beerconnoisseur.com/beer-styles/american-lager"><stro=
ng>American Lager</strong></a>: IBUs =E2=80=93 5-10</p>



<p><strong>Wheat Beer/Hefeweizen</strong>: IBUs =E2=80=93 10-15</p>



<p><strong>Blonde Ale</strong>: IBUs =E2=80=93 15-30</p>



<p><strong>Amber Ale</strong>: IBUs =E2=80=93 20-40</p>



<p><strong>India Pale Ale (IPA)</strong>: IBUs =E2=80=93 40-70</p>



<p><strong>Hazy IPA</strong>: IBUs =E2=80=93 30-70</p>



<p><strong>Double IPA</strong>: IBUs =E2=80=93 60-100</p>



<p><strong>American Pale Ale</strong>: IBUs =E2=80=93 30-50</p>



<p><strong>Imperial Stout</strong>: IBUs =E2=80=93 50-90</p>



<p><strong>Belgian Tripel</strong>: IBUs- 20-45</p>



<p><strong>Pilsner</strong>: IBUs =E2=80=93 25-45</p>



<p><strong>Porter</strong>: IBUs =E2=80=93 25-50</p>



